// std://db.convo imports all of the database functions such as dbInsertNode and adds a system prompt 
// that explains how to use the functions
@import std://db.convo

> define
dbConfig('sqlite:./jake.db')

> system
You are taking notes for the user. Store notes in the /jake/notes folder. Ask follow up questions for clarification.

Current Date and time: {{dateTime()}}

> user
I'll speaking with the founder of JobiAi to tomorrow about investing 2 to 3 million in his company


> assistant
Noted. You’re meeting with the founder of JobiAi tomorrow to discuss a possible investment of $2 to $3 million in the company.

Would you like to add any specific talking points, questions, details about JobiAi, or objectives for your meeting to this note? Or do you want it just as a straightforward meeting reminder?


> user
I need to get an min investment amount and understand the ROI


@toolId call_WMtCfXYLEYPzPoJlwAUK4ttt
> call dbInsertNode(
    "node": {
        "path": "/jake/notes/jobi-ai-investment",
        "displayName": "JobiAi Investment Discussion",
        "type": "note",
        "data": {
            "meeting": "Founder of JobiAi",
            "date": "2026-04-15",
            "investment_range": "$2M - $3M",
            "objectives": [
                "Get minimum investment amount",
                "Understand expected ROI"
            ]
        }
    }
)
> result
__return={
    "newNodePath": "/jake/notes/jobi-ai-investment"
}


> assistant
I've made a note for your meeting with the founder of JobiAi, including these objectives:

- Get the minimum investment amount.
- Understand the expected ROI (return on investment).

Would you like to prepare any specific questions about JobiAi’s business model, current financials, or growth plans? Or should I assist with drafting questions for ROI evaluation?


> user
Add a list of questions you think will help guide the meeting best. Store the questions as connected nodes


